methods.canParse:
Checks if this parser can parse value.

 
null values are always return true.

:param value: (java.lang.String) - the value
:return: (boolean) true if the value can be parsed.
methods.epochAny21stCentury:
Returns four parser that will parse long values as epoch seconds, epoch milliseconds, epoch microseconds, and
 epoch nanoseconds from the 21st century.

:param longParser: (io.deephaven.csv.Parser<java.lang.Long>) - the long parser
:return: (java.util.List<io.deephaven.csv.Parser<java.time.Instant>>) the 21st century epoch second, milli, micro, and nanoseconds parsers
methods.epochAnyParser:
Returns four parsers that will parse long values as epoch seconds, milliseconds, epoch microseconds, and epoch
 nanoseconds based on non-overlapping min/max ranges.

 
 Note: the duration between the epoch and the max must be less than 1000 times the duration between the epoch and
 the min.

:param longParser: (io.deephaven.csv.Parser<java.lang.Long>) - the long parser
:param min: (java.time.Instant) - the minimum instant to infer
:param max: (java.time.Instant) - the maximum instant to infer
:return: (java.util.List<io.deephaven.csv.Parser<java.time.Instant>>) the epoch milli and micro parsers

methods.parse:
Parses value when non-null, otherwise returns null.

 
 This method catches RuntimeException from function and converts them to Parser.ParserException.

:param value: (java.lang.String) - the string to parse
:return: (Parser.T) the parsed value, or null

text: A parser is responsible for parsing strings into parsed types.
